news.title: Leasing of retail spaces rise 55% across top eight cities to over 24 lakh sq ft in Q4 FY25: Report
news.para: "India's retail sector is evolving at a dynamic pace, and the strong leasing activity in Q1 2025 reflects growing market confidence," Saurabh Shatdal, Managing Director, Capital Markets and Head-Retail, India said.

news.title: Cement prices expected to rise in April 2025 as government spending increases
news.para: The financial services company further added in the report that, following a dip in prices in March after three months of improvement, the outlook for the coming months appears more optimistic.

news.title: Keystone Realtors reports pre-sales of ₹30.28 billion in FY25
news.para: In Q4 FY25, Keystone Realtors recorded pre-sales of ₹8.54 billion as against ₹8.43 billion reported in Q4 FY24. Collections for Q4 FY25 were at ₹7.46 billion as compared to ₹6.70 billion in Q4 FY24, showing a quarterly growth of 11 per cent year-on-year.

news.title: Godrej Properties' booking value grows 31% to ₹29.444 crore in FY25
news.para: This was achieved through the sale of 15,302 homes with a total area of 25.73 million sq ft, a year-on-year volume growth of 29 per cent.

news.title: Thane collector identifies 10 land parcels to rehabilitate SGNP slum-dwellers
news.para: Only the Thane collector identified 10 parcels of land between 85.57 hectares and 7.15 hectares in area in the district to rehabilitate slum-dwellers of SGNP.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC directs MDDA vice-chairman to clarify illegal constructions in Rishikesh
news.para: The Garhwal commissioner and the Mussoorie-Dehradun Development Authority (MDDA) vice-chairman appeared before a division bench of Chief Justice G Narendar and Justice Pankaj Purohit via videoconferencing.

news.title: Madurai civic body announces 5% rebate on property tax payments before April 30
news.para: In a statement, the corporation urged residents to take advantage of the limited time offer by ensuring their property tax is paid on or before the deadline.

news.title: Property owners in Bengaluru complain against 25-30% hike in tax rates
news.para: BBMP introduces new charges and penalties as citizens question lack of transparency

news.title: Bhubaneswar: BDA announces two new housing projects in Khurda district
news.para: The announcement, made during BDA's 150th authority meeting recently, was particularly welcomed by middle-income buyers who were waiting for such govt housing initiatives, especially near Bhubaneswar.

news.title: Brigade Group to jointly develop 10 acres land in Mysuru
news.para: The project has a gross development value (GDV) of approximately ₹225 crore and a total development potential of 0.37 million sq ft. It will feature plots spanning over eight acres, and apartments spread over two acres.

news.title: Arkade Developers to redevelop four housing societies in Mumbai
news.para: The company registered the development agreement (DA) for Satya Shreepal Nagar A CHS, Om Shreepal Nagar B & C CHS, Sheetal Shreepal CHS and Sai Shreepal CHS.

news.title: Priyanka Chopra’s family lease out property in Pune at ₹2.25 lakh per month
news.para: The transaction incurred a stamp duty payment of ₹39,000 and registration charges of ₹1,000, according to the Inspector General of Registration (IGR) documents reviewed by Square Yards.

news.title: ED searches premises of Tamil Nadu minister in case against TVH Group
news.para: K N Nehru is the Tamil Nadu minister for municipal administration. The sources said the premises of the minister, whose son Arun Nehru is a Lok Sabha MP, were also covered during the raids that are continuing.

news.title: Chennai: TNUHDB renovates 8,352 flats in Perumbakkam for Rs 70 crore
news.para: A flagship initiative under this plan is the 170 crore renovation of 62,197 apartment units maintained by the board in Chennai and nearby areas.

news.title: Karnataka government introduces A-khata and B-khata framework in Kalaburagi
news.para: Priyank Kharge, minister for rural development and panchayat raj and Kalaburagi district in-charge, confirmed that this initiative will establish asset ownership rights.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Women purchased properties worth Rs 38,000 crore in FY25
news.para: Indore recorded property acquisitions worth Rs 6,300 crore by women in the last financial year. During this period, an impressive 35,988 sale deeds were registered in women's names.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government allows self-certification of stilt + two-floor residences
news.para: The initiative expands on the existing single-window system that allows immediate online approval for ground + 1 floor houses.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government forms committee to complete Jaypee projects
news.para: This follows the Allahabad high court's March 10 order, upholding the Authority's 2020 decision to cancel the allotment of 1,000 hectares of land along the Yamuna Expressway to JAL over unpaid dues.

news.title: Century Real Estate touch ₹1,800 crore revenue in FY25
news.para: Century Real Estate is planning to launch about five residential projects in the financial year 2025-26 and about two million sq ft of commercial real estate projects.

news.title: Leasing of industrial & logistics spaces rise 18% in 24 cities in Q4 FY25: Savills
news.para: Real estate consultant Savills India data showed that Tier-I cities accounted for 79 per cent of the leasing activities, while Tier-II and Tier-III cities contributed 21 per cent.
